<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871221-0106 </DOCNO><HL> Foothill Alters Standstill Pact</HL><DD> 12/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> FGI TEPTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> LOS ANGELES  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Foothill Group Inc., a commercial finance concern, said it amended its standstill agreement with two units of Tucson Electric Power Corp. to allow the units to purchase as much as 40% of Foothill.    Foothill said the Tucson, Ariz.-based utility's Santa Cruz Resources Inc. and Sierrita Resources Inc. units have informed Foothill that their holding currently is close to the previous limit of 30%. The units also indicated that they intend to buy additional shares, Foothill said.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading Friday, Foothill shares closed at $4.75, up 50 cents. </TEXT></DOC>